Western Cape police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Andr Traut said that police had been alerted at 6.15am about a robbery in progress at the mall and had reacted swiftly. Upon their arrival on the scene four suspects made an attempt to flee. Police managed to apprehend three of the four aged 32 41 and 41 and confiscate two prohibited firearms. The fourth suspect evaded arrest and is being sought Traut said.The suspects who are from Makhaza Khayelitsha are due to appear court once they have been charged he added.